The paper discusses a new indicator of scientific prestige for journals, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The mention of the Plan Nacional de Investigacion Cientifica suggests a focus on research and development, which could be related to databases (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of indicators and metrics could also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and social networks (cs.SI). Finally, the mention of the Fondo Social Europeo suggests a focus on digital libraries (cs.DL), which could be related to the dissemination and impact of scientific publications.
